"{\"uid\": \"thenationaldesk.com-news-americas-news-now-olympics-organizers-apologize-for-drag-queen-last-supper-parody-really-sorry-paris-2024-christianity-catholicism-religion-jesus-christ-apostles-olympic-opening-ceremonies\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"byJACKSON WALKER | The National Desk  TOPICS:  PARIS (TND) -Organizers of the Paris Olympics apologized Sunday after an apparent reenactment of \\\"The Last Supper\\\" by drag performers drew international ire.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_National_Desk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The National Desk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_National_Desk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_National_Desk\"}, {\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_dinar\", \"score\": 0.9997759785164456, \"rank\": 0.0002240716805074349, \"text\": \"TND\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_dinar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_dinar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Friday performance came during a floating parade along the River Seine commemorating the beginning of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the parade, a group of performers dressed in drag appeared to invoke Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" a famous painting depicting a scene from the Gospel of John in which Jesus Christ announces one of his apostles will betray him.\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5926370833683518e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.997462865077236, \"rank\": 0.002543588143581762, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taking to X, the official Olympic Games account explainedthe scene aimed to make viewers \\\"aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.\\\"\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, major figures such as House Speaker Mike Johnson, X owner Elon Musk and Kansas City Chiefs kicker Harrison Butker expressed outrage, describing the scene as a mockery of Christianity.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 753, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 0.9999984891280792, \"rank\": 1.3914086010201652e-06, \"text\": \"House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kansas_City_Chiefs\", \"score\": 0.9997278082943283, \"rank\": 0.0002521779762325962, \"text\": \"Kansas City Chiefs\", \"types\": 